Tate Data R
-----------

Exploring the Tate's collection dataset with R and Knitr.

By Rob Myers <rob@robmyers.org> .

Dependencies
------------

The R programming language.

The R libraries ggplot2, grid, igraph, knitr and tm .

The tate-data project: https://gitorious.org/robmyers/tate-data

(This project repository should be checked out next to the tate-data one, at the same level.)

How To Use
----------

Install the dependencies.

Run make.

View the resulting PDFs and HTML files.

Pre-made PDF and HTML files are included in this repositort.

Products
--------

PDFs of visualizations are placed in /pdf .

Rendered HTML of report documents are placed in /html .
